# KMP Platform SDK — Project Rules (Index)

This repository uses **Cursor rules** under `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` for maintainable, scoped guidance.

Keep this file short. **Prefer extending an existing `.mdc` in the same domain** (e.g. Kotlin syntax → `kotlin-style.mdc`) instead of adding many tiny one-topic files; add a **new** `.mdc` when the topic is a new area (KDoc, tests, architecture, …).

## Core principles (always on)

- **Precedence:** project rules in this repo override conflicting Cursor User Rules. What matters for contributors is under `.cursor/rules/` (committed), not personal global rules.
- This is a **Kotlin Multiplatform library (SDK)** — not a standalone app. Avoid hardcoded app assumptions; prefer configuration via constructor parameters (and optional wiring in `sample/*`).
- **FQN in Kotlin code is forbidden**: do not write fully qualified names in expressions/type annotations/generics; use imports (or typealiases). Only keep minimal FQN when imports are impossible/ambiguous, and explain the reason in PR/commit message.
- Never suggest or run tests automatically after test changes.

## Detailed rules live in `.cursor/rules/`

- `project-overview.mdc` — project identity, stack, repo/module layout, boundaries.
- `architecture-patterns.mdc` — wiring/bootstrap conventions, layering, networking, errors.
- `docs-kdoc-basics.mdc` + `docs-kdoc-type-requirements.mdc` — **mandatory** KDoc and documentation rules (package/path doc requests: **definition of done** is in `docs-kdoc-basics.mdc`, including **every public interface member** unless the user narrows scope).
- `localization.mdc` — Compose localization resource layout and naming.
- `testing-style.mdc` — test conventions/constraints (if/when tests exist).
- `testing-compose-preview-no-tests.mdc` — no UI/unit tests for Preview-only helpers (`PreviewParameterProvider`, etc.).
- `kotlin-style.mdc` — Kotlin syntax: `when` subject / naming outcomes, `if`+`return` braces (no one-line `if (…) return`).
- `ai-workflow.mdc` — dependency changes guidance and SDK vs sample boundaries.
